{% extends "demo.html.j2" %}

{% block head_extra %}
<link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ asset_base | default('') }}assets/s7-provenance.css">
{% endblock %}

{% set default_key = card_data.meta.default_state %}
{% set default_state = card_data.states[default_key] %}
{% set default_scenario = card_data.scenarios[default_state.scenario] %}
{% set latest_audit = card_data.states['hedge-fund|latest|audit'] %}
{% set restatement = latest_audit.vintage_findings
  | selectattr('finding_type', 'equalto', 'return-restatement') | first %}

{% block demo_content %}
<aside class="s7-disclosure" role="note">
  <strong>Synthetic, fictional demonstration.</strong>
  <span>{{ card_data.meta.fictional_disclosure }} Availability varies by manager, vehicle,
    source right, and decision date.</span>
</aside>

<section class="exhibit-intro" aria-label="What this exhibit shows">
  <h2 class="exhibit-intro__title">What this exhibit shows</h2>
  <div class="exhibit-intro__block">
    <h3 class="exhibit-intro__sub">The answer</h3>
    <p><strong>A track record is usable only after each observation has a known owner,
      date, and comparable economic basis.</strong> In the opening example, three monthly
      returns can enter a comparable panel. Other records stay outside because identity,
      lineage, or fee basis is unresolved.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="exhibit-intro__block">
    <h3 class="exhibit-intro__sub">How to read it</h3>
    <ul class="exhibit-intro__list">
      <li>Follow the opening flow from supplied observations through identity and basis checks.</li>
      <li>Compare effective date with first-known date before using a revised value.</li>
      <li>Use the controls only to inspect another precomputed source shape or evidence view.</li>
      <li>Open the <a href="{{ asset_base | default('') }}specs/{{ card.id }}.html">technical
        method and provenance</a> for the full admission and comparability rules.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="s7-opening" aria-labelledby="s7-opening-title">
  <header>
    <p class="s7-kicker">Complete opening example</p>
    <h2 id="s7-opening-title">Can the early hedge-fund record support a comparable panel?</h2>
    <p>{{ default_scenario.source_shape }} Only evidence available by
      <time datetime="{{ default_state.decision_at }}">31 March 2024</time> is considered.</p>
  </header>

  <div class="s7-flow" aria-label="Source observations pass through identity and basis checks before entering or staying outside the panel">
    <article class="s7-flow__step s7-flow__step--source">
      <span>1</span>
      <div><h3>Source observations</h3><p>Versioned composite returns, terms, and
        predecessor evidence arrive with their original dates.</p></div>
    </article>
    <article class="s7-flow__step s7-flow__step--checks">
      <span>2</span>
      <div><h3>Identity and basis checks</h3>
        <p><strong>{{ default_state.lineage_segments[0].observation_ids | length }} records attach to one exact lineage segment.</strong>
          Each candidate observation must also match the entity, membership, frequency,
          calendar, currency, fee, benchmark, and valuation basis.</p></div>
    </article>
    <div class="s7-flow__outcomes">
      <article class="s7-outcome s7-outcome--admitted">
        <span>3A</span><div><h3>Admitted panel</h3>
          <p><strong>{{ default_state.panel.rows | length }} comparable monthly returns</strong>
            retain their dates and reported net basis.</p></div>
      </article>
      <article class="s7-outcome s7-outcome--excluded">
        <span>3B</span><div><h3>Kept out</h3>
          <p><strong>{{ default_state.exclusions | length }} records stay outside that lineage.</strong>
            One return is excluded because it is reported on an incompatible fee basis.</p></div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="s7-boundary"><strong>Decision boundary:</strong> Documented lineage is not
    evidence that historical skill transferred.</p>
</section>

<section class="s7-clock" aria-labelledby="s7-clock-title">
  <div>
    <p class="s7-kicker">Two clocks, two different questions</p>
    <h2 id="s7-clock-title">A revision belongs to February but was not knowable until September</h2>
    <p>The economic period and the publication date must remain separate. The later
      publication date prevents this revision from entering an earlier decision.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="s7-clock__timeline" role="img" aria-label="A return restatement is effective on 29 February 2024 and first known on 15 September 2024.">
    <article>
      <span>Effective date</span>
      <strong><time datetime="{{ restatement.effective_at }}">29 February 2024</time></strong>
      <small>When the revised return belongs economically</small>
    </article>
    <div class="s7-clock__line" aria-hidden="true"><span></span></div>
    <article>
      <span>First known</span>
      <strong><time datetime="{{ restatement.first_known_at }}">15 September 2024</time></strong>
      <small>When an allocator could first have used it</small>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="s7-controls" aria-label="Explore a precomputed provenance state">
  <fieldset>
    <legend>Source shape</legend>
    {% for token in ['public-equity', 'hedge-fund', 'credit', 'private-market'] %}
    <button type="button" data-s7-scenario-control="{{ token }}"
      aria-pressed="{{ 'true' if token == default_state.scenario else 'false' }}">
      {{ card_data.scenarios[token].label }}
    </button>
    {% endfor %}
  </fieldset>
  <fieldset>
    <legend>Decision date</legend>
    <button type="button" data-s7-cutoff-control="early" aria-pressed="true">Earlier</button>
    <button type="button" data-s7-cutoff-control="latest" aria-pressed="false">Later</button>
  </fieldset>
  <fieldset>
    <legend>Evidence view</legend>
    <button type="button" data-s7-view-control="lineage" aria-pressed="true">Lineage</button>
    <button type="button" data-s7-view-control="basis" aria-pressed="false">Comparability</button>
    <button type="button" data-s7-view-control="audit" aria-pressed="false">Revision history</button>
  </fieldset>
</section>

<details class="s7-explorer">
  <summary>Explore another evidence state</summary>
  <div class="s7-explorer__body">
    <p class="s7-notice" role="status" data-s7-notice hidden></p>
    <p class="s7-announcer" aria-live="polite" data-s7-announcer>
      Showing the hedge-fund composite at the earlier decision date, with the lineage view.
    </p>
    <header>
      <p class="s7-kicker" data-s7-view-label>Lineage</p>
      <h2 data-s7-scenario-label>{{ default_scenario.label }}</h2>
      <p data-s7-explorer-summary>{{ default_state.conclusion }}</p>
    </header>
    <div class="s7-explorer__result" data-s7-explorer-body>
      <article><span>Exact lineage segments</span><strong>{{ default_state.lineage_segments | length }}</strong></article>
      <article><span>Records attached to the lineage</span><strong>{{ default_state.lineage_segments[0].observation_ids | length }}</strong></article>
      <article><span>Records kept outside</span><strong>{{ default_state.exclusions | length }}</strong></article>
      <p>{{ default_state.what_changed }}</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</details>

<section class="s7-limit" aria-labelledby="s7-limit-title">
  <h2 id="s7-limit-title">What this method refuses</h2>
  <p>This inspection decides what may enter a later analysis. It does not estimate alpha,
    Sharpe ratio, IRR, PME, skill, or manager rank. If identity, membership, comparability,
    or point-in-time evidence is incomplete, it preserves the exclusion instead of silently
    repairing the history.</p>
</section>

<noscript>
  <p class="s7-noscript">The complete opening example remains available above. The exploration
    controls require JavaScript.</p>
</noscript>
{% endblock %}

{% block methodology %}
<p>The method selects only evidence knowable at the decision date, attaches each observation
  to one effective entity lineage, and checks a complete economic-basis signature before panel
  admission. A separate all-versions view reveals later backfills and restatements.</p>
<p>Displayed returns and cash-flow values are source observations or deterministic currency
  transformations, not estimates. Browser code only selects an exact precomputed state.</p>
{% endblock %}

{% block body_scripts %}
<script src="{{ asset_base | default('') }}assets/s7-provenance.js"></script>
{% endblock %}
